uters and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Pope</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Encyclical</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Religion and Belief</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Jeremy Nixon</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Leo XIV</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Christopher Olah</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">A.G.I. House</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Catholic Church</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/05/27/multimedia/00biz-agi-house-Jeremy-Nixon1-bkwg/00biz-agi-house-Jeremy-Nixon1-bkwg-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Kelsey McClellan for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Jeremy Nixon at A.G.I. House, which he founded in San Francisco’s Twin Peaks.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Our Field Trip to Google I/O + A Sit-Down With Sundar Pichai + System Update</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/22/podcasts/our-field-trip-to-google-i-o-a-sit-down-with-sundar-pichai-system-update.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/22/podcasts/our-field-trip-to-google-i-o-a-sit-down-with-sundar-pichai-system-update.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/22/podcasts/our-field-trip-to-google-i-o-a-sit-down-with-sundar-pichai-system-update.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>“This is the on